OOC: In case you haven't noticed, the majority of dinosaurs are by 
definition rather lumbering.  The triceratops is no exception.  No 
offense, you just didn't exactly pick the most nimble of beast forms.

Reaching the stretch of ocean seperating the two continents, Empath 
halts.  She studies the gap, which might as well be a crevasse 
considering that none of them have hover capability.  After a 
moment's consideration, she transforms to jet mode, figuring the same 
thrust that can take her to the speed of sound is quite capable of 
transporting the three of them across the water.  "Climb on," she 
instructs her companions.
